    "A measurement of the ancilla register then produces the desired state |x⟩ with probability |c| 2 = O(1/κ 2).",
    "Thus, to produce |x⟩, it suffices to create O(κ 2) copies of |b⟩ and make Õ(κ) queries to U A for each copy, for a total of Õ(κ 3) queries.",
    "In principle, these copies could be processed in parallel, and, as described above, our method offers a minimal-depth approach for preparing |b⟩⊗(O(κ 2))with only O(N) ancillae.",
    "Using amplitude amplification, the number of queries to U A can be reduced to Õ(κ 2), which would involve O(κ) serial reflections about the state |b⟩, an operation that can be performed optimally by our protocol (see App.",
    "Finally, using variable-time amplitude amplification [14,34] or ideas from adiabatic quantum computing [45,46], the U A query complexity can be further reduced to O(κ)."
